line_1: The Tree of Life was thence to Heav'n remov'd:
line_2: THE Tree of Knowlege we in Eden prov'd;

line_1: Those dusty Characters he soon remov'd;
line_2: Their grave starch'd Morals then unuseful prov'd,

line_1: But when in after-times (be far remov'd
line_2: That day) our Monarch, glorious and belov'd,

line_1: 'T was pinch'd, it roar'd, and every doubt removed.
line_2: "Was't dead or living?" This was fairly proved, —

line_1: Yet far was he from stoic pride removed;
line_2: He felt humanely, and he warmly loved:

line_1: And his harp and his bays to Hibernia remov'd;
line_2: Apollo hath quitted the isle he once lov'd,

line_1: Her surest patrons are remov'd,
line_2: And her triumphant foes approv'd.

line_1: Thus from Crouds, and Noise remov'd,
line_2: Let each Moment be improv'd;

line_1: And then her court to Babylon remov'd:
line_2: The queen a while had these diversions prov'd,

line_1: In nature near, tho' far by space remov'd;
line_2: Are her compatriots all; by her belov'd,

line_1: His Flocks he straight to Ida's Plains remov'd;
line_2: When to the fickle Youth, I own'd I lov'd,

line_1: Yet was the veil mysterious ne'er remov'd,
line_2: From him th' admiring, and from her the lov'd,

line_1: " And soon each trace of indigence remov'd.
line_2: " He found me friendless, pitied me, and lov'd:

line_1: Till from my Sight you cautiously remov'd,
line_2: Then, not till then, I knew how well I lov'd:

line_1: There hid in loath'd obscurity, remov'd
line_2: From pleasures left, but never more belov'd,

line_1: There Hangs a Second, and not far Remov'd,
line_2: A Third lies poison'd, who false Celia Lov'd.

line_1: And not for ev'ry trifling Farce remov'd.
line_2: My small Attempts to please were then approv'd,

line_2: Pride of my life, esteemed, beloved,

line_1: The First, who, from his native soil remov'd,

line_1: From there sweet scenes I found myself remov'd,
line_2: I fear'd no more remember'd or belov'd.

line_2: When best enjoy'd, when most improv'd.

line_1: From fields and groves to palaces remov'd;
line_2: Great ones the pleasing exercise approv'd;

line_1: The Darling of my Soul so soon remov'd?
line_2: The only valu'd, and the best belov'd.
